  "texts": [
    "Aspect terms (a) refers to specific characteristics of the entity or topic being evaluated or discussed, which can be explicitly or implicitly mentioned and can be associated with different categories or domains.",
    "For example, for a mobile phone, possible aspects include taking pictures, making calls, browsing the internet, and attributes such as color, size, and weight.",
    "Categories (c) refers to the broader field or domain to which an aspect belongs.",
    "It can be predefined or extracted from the text, and it helps contextualize the SA results.",
    "For example, categories could be design or brand for the laptop domain."
  ],
